		<div id="welcomeDiv"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
			<p>Fill the five-litre jug and then pour it into the three-litre jug. The five-litre jug has 2 litres left. Now throw the three-litre jug of water away. Pour the 2 litres from the five-litre jug to the three-litre jug. So now the three-litre jug has just 2 litres of water. Fill the five-litre jug again, and pour 1 litre to the three-litre jug. You are then left with 4 litres of water in the five-litre jug.</p>
		</div>
